<paragraph id="D10D36F999132B22BC86FEC9FD18FED0" blockId="20.[159,762,311,1398]" box="[197,721,311,335]" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">Diagnosis — (Male unknown). As for genus.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F999132B22BC86FE9BFE68FC13" blockId="20.[159,762,311,1398]" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">
Description — Dorsum soft. All coxal setae slender; medial margin of Cx-III almost as long as medial margin of Cx-IV. Genital bay very shallow, gonopore very long, genital plates broad and rounded, with 5 pairs of small acetabula arranged along the plate margins, medial margin straight or slightly concave, pregenital sclerite small, triangular (
<figureCitation id="49892A7C99132B22BC93FDA5FE91FDEC" box="[208,344,603,627]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="19.[159,171,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[252,1338,451,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-6@19.[242,1346,451,1711]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11: Schwoerbelia pioniformis n. gen., n. sp., female, Bach MAE National Park, Vietnam: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B-C – palp; D – gnathosoma; E – I-L-5 and -6; F – IV-L. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396012/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">Figure 11A</figureCitation>
); excretory pore smooth. P-3 with a very long lateral seta, P-4 with two long setae close to each other, and a peg-like mediodistal seta (
<figureCitation id="49892A7C99132B22BCE4FD3AFEE8FD43" box="[167,289,708,732]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="19.[159,171,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[252,1338,451,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-6@19.[242,1346,451,1711]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11: Schwoerbelia pioniformis n. gen., n. sp., female, Bach MAE National Park, Vietnam: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B-C – palp; D – gnathosoma; E – I-L-5 and -6; F – IV-L. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396012/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">Figures 11</figureCitation>
B-C); P-5 long (around 80 % L of P-4); gnathosoma with posterior anchoral process. Legs: number of swimming setae: I-L-1, 1 (short); II-L-4, 2; II-L-5, 2-3; III-L-4, 3; III-L-5, 3; IV-L-4, 3; IV-L-5, 3-4; IV-L-3-5 each with one strong ventrodistal pennate seta (
<figureCitation id="49892A7C99132B22BD57FC8DFE5DFC13" box="[276,404,883,908]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="19.[159,171,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[252,1338,451,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-6@19.[242,1346,451,1711]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11: Schwoerbelia pioniformis n. gen., n. sp., female, Bach MAE National Park, Vietnam: A – idiosoma, ventral view; B-C – palp; D – gnathosoma; E – I-L-5 and -6; F – IV-L. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396012/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">Figure 11F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F999132B22BC86FC5DFD94FB4C" blockId="20.[159,762,311,1398]" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">Measurements — Idiosoma L/W 638/538; coxal field L/W 253/291; genital field L/W 165/214; genital plate L/W 51-52/38; gonopore L 148, pregenital sclerite W 29. Palp: total L 179, dL/H, dL/H ratio: P-1, 19/25, 0.75; P-2, 49/39, 1.28; P-3, 31/30, 1.05; P- 4, 48/22, 2.2; P-5, 32/12, 2.6; dL ratio P-2/P-4, 1.03; gnathosoma vL 49, with anchoral process 85; chelicera total L 75. Legs: dL of I-L: 41, 48, 66, 91, 98, 103; dL of IV-L: 52, 55, 68, 97, 115, 119.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F999132B22BC86FB17FD55FABB" blockId="20.[159,762,311,1398]" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">
Etymology — The name of the new species refers to its resemblance with 
<taxonomicName id="16B24D7A99132B22BDBEFAF3FD55FABB" box="[509,668,1292,1316]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Piona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99132B22BDBEFAF3FDF2FABB" box="[509,571,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">Piona</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D10D36F999132B22BC86FAC5FE02FAE9" blockId="20.[159,762,311,1398]" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">
Distribution — 
<collectingCountry id="A9A5766999132B22BDC1FAC5FE21FACC" box="[386,488,1339,1363]" name="Vietnam" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
; known only from the 
<emphasis id="E3C6EAEB99132B22BCDCFAA0FEE2FAE9" box="[159,299,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">locus typicus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="49892A7C99132B22BD79FAA0FE76FAE9" box="[314,447,1374,1398]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="39.[159,171,1846,1865]" captionTargetBox="[265,1323,302,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-6@39.[265,1323,302,1814]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 25: Photoghraphs of sampling sites: A – Laos, Kauangxi Waterfall (locus typicus of Monatractides laosensis n. sp., Hexaxonopsis laosensis n. sp., Sinaxonopsis laosensis n. sp. and Africasia purpurea n. sp.); B – Laos, Kouangxi Waterfall, pond behind artifical barrier (sampling site of Hygrobates hamatus K. Viets, 1935, H. henni Wiles, 2004 and locus typicus of Forelia gereckei n. sp.); C – Vietnam, Bach MAE National Park, brook with a pool (sampling site of Monatarctides sp. and locus typicus of Limnesia scharfi n. sp., Schwoerbelia pioniformis n. sp. and Arrenurus contortus n. sp.; D – Cambodia, moat around the main Angkor temple (locus typicus of Hexaxonopsis" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396054/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="412">Figure 25C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
